			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Admittedly I havent gone around trying to pvp and I have talked to many higher mages online to see if they are better at pvp than me (and all of them said that they havent been sucessful but it does get better at higher lvls) but being lvl 62 on a pvp all my pvp experiences is that mages cant defend themselves and their pets are totoally useless (only in pvp).
<br />

<br />
I am usually sucessful if i attack first and its against a caster. ( Except for necro.  Necros just heal themselves on your hps and kill you LOL)
<br />

<br />
I had 3 accounts a 30 necro enchanter and mage.  Necro consisently killed my mage even up to 34 when he was still 30.
<br />

<br />
At lower lvls (under 20) its true most respect mages cause their pet is something to deal with and the hp spread isnt that much different.
<br />

<br />
over that though for me its changed.  Pet usually get feared, rooted or ignored (melee class). 
<br />
 
<br />
Pets? well they never keep up with the target even with velocity on.  They also stop to cast wwhich further increases the distance.
<br />

<br />
Heres the picture Mage is running from the attacker, attacker is running after mage and banging him, pet is far behind trying to catchup to  hit the attacker.
<br />

<br />
anyways no more ranting heres my problem.
<br />

<br />
Melee - usually quad for 250-400 at 1600 hps they kill me in about 3 seconds or less with virtue (3000 hps) I might last 6 seconds.
<br />
Pet?? they laugh at it!
<br />

<br />
In fact I have head melee brag that they have never had a problem killing a int based character oppenly in ooc and no one said any different!
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Now to my second problem it seems that most stratigies for mages mostly come down to running or gating.
<br />

<br />
I feel that having to run from a conflict is cowardly.  But  when i run they  are faster than me so they kill me anyways.  I swear even If i have sow on im toast .  I have made sure my weight is low (19) out of 75 and they still are right behind me banging away.
<br />

<br />
to gate means u must have set your self up in the zone (which means u are probably there to pvp).  Gate has saved my bacon against casting characters, but have u ever tried to gate with someone quading you for 300?  Sounds like a dead mage to me....   or am i wrong?
