			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The real question is "What can I do when I get jumped unprepared and doing something else at that point in time". The answer is not much, what you can do is keep yourself aware of your surroundings.
<br />

<br />
For instance do a /who every 5-10 seconds. It gets to be a habbit. Notice any high level enemies in the zone (and you need to know them by name, they will go anon. Also /guildstatus is your friend), if so make sure you are prepared to get jumped. This means you have a high level SoW stacked deep in your buff slots, have your DMG shield and resists applied and have the pet ready and fully buffed. Now here is a trick I like to do, make a hotkey that says /pet attack playername where you put in the name of your potential enemy in the zone. Just spam this while your at the camp and as soon as your enemy is within range your pet will go after them. Puts them on the defensive right away.
<br />

<br />
Another trick is if you have a bard in your group make him get the adventure while the rest of the group heads to the dungeon locations. Bards can get an adventure even under a serious enemy bombardment.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
