				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thanks rancar, very resonable responce - treat everyone as an enemy untill proved otherwise - wont make many friends that way..... but that is life on talon zek.  
<br />

<br />
1.  Be prepared - know your surroundings and the dangers in it.  
<br />

<br />
I realize that when i am in a pvp zone (and not being lazy) I always have pet up buffed and velocitied.  It will deter some ppl from attacking just because ti is there and may give me a few seconds to exit gracefully. As well i always have sow (are there different lvls of sow?) or my jboots on and clickable with my buffs.  I always buy virtue and c3 and bury them deep.  Which is a god send against other casters and buys time against melee.  I also always load my pvp spells up - I am never unprepared.
<br />

<br />
I guess the important thing here is to do /who and guildstat and aggro pet on them before they get close, especially if they are a known enemy - that is one downfall i dont do presently And I do have known ppl that kill me continously when im in their zone (when i ask them why - they say its because they can and I respect that ) and those that try to kill me and havent suceeded yet - but have made it their goal.
<br />

<br />
Most melee ignore pets - damage is low and if u kill the caster the pet disappears.  Lets not forget that anyone that gets to a high enough lvl to attack a 62 isnt a newbie on talon zek.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
second sceario :  You have spotted the potential enemy in zone your pet has aggroed and thumping him (albeit poorly) and he has run over to you and started thumping you.  Is there any alternate to running?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
