			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For your second scenario:
<br />

<br />
The second you see your pet take off from your attack spam assist your pet and start casting annul magic. I usually follow this with a click of my bio orb, you would be suprised who you can blind after an annul or two (especially if they are unprepared). If blind lands its FoT time.
<br />

<br />
If your blind is useless your melee opponent might not be 100% sure where you are unless they have trak or are hacking. What I do in this instance is keep a cloudy potion hotkeyed, you can invis on the run with them and if you invis while hillbugging (rapidly changing direction at the top of a crest, can do it even on small hills like those in BBM) you will show up as being on the hill to any traker (and anyone who hacks). So basically I instant reclaim my pet while on the run, hill bug and invis myself which should cause ghosting to occur for even the best melees. Try and get a speed advantage on my drogmor, unpop my suspended pet and make my second round of attacks.
<br />

<br />
This only applies to people that are chronic hackers. I know most of them by name so it is worth it to me to bug their SEQ or MQ. If I am fighting an honest player I don't invis myself or kill my pet. If they are a hacker they will constantly circle around the hill you dissapeared on as their program will show you as being there (same thing with track). Then I just come up from behind, break invis, unsuspend pet and start a FoT. Follow up with chains of scars of sigil.
<br />

<br />
You can usually tell right off the bat if you have a decent shot. If the melee is on a 100k horse and you are using a sow potion use the distance you just gained to gate away. I also cannot recommend a high level horse enough. It literally changes the landscape of mage PvP, they are undispellable and the 100k/seru horses are faster snared than most sows. Because I two box a bard and mage I play my mage like a bard in PvP. Run around a ton and use speed and ghosting (the legal kind) to my advantage whenever possible. I'm not the best at PvP with my mage (there are mages on SZ that far surpass me) but I am suprisingly decent.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
